Females of Pseudopoda lacrimosa sp. n. could be included in the Pseudopoda diversipunctata -group ( Jaeger , 2001). Females of this group are characterized by: lateral lobes of epigyne touching each other only at posterior part, the first winding of internal duct system running from laterally to the median line and the loop situated ventrally (
Jaeger 2001
). On the other hand, males of Pseudopoda lacrimosa sp. n. have long embolic projection and tip, which could place them in the Pseudopoda latembola -group ( Jaeger , 2001).
